documentation": ["*boost_module* is a codepy.BoostPythonModule containing host code\nwhich calls CUDA code.\nCurrent limitations of nvcc preclude compiling anything which\nreferences Boost by nvcc, so the code needs to be split in two pieces:\na BoostPythonModule compiled by the host C++ compiler, as well as CUDA\ncode which is compiled by nvcc.  This module allows the construction of\nCUDA code to be compiled by nvcc, as well as bridges between the CUDA\ncode and the BoostPythonModule."]}, {"name": "codepy.cuda.CudaModule.add_to_preamble", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pa", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.cuda.CudaModule.add_to_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "body", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add the {class}`cgen.Generable` instances in the iterable\n*body* to the body of the module *self*.\n"]}, {"name": "codepy.cuda.CudaModule.add_function", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add a function to be exposed to code in the BoostPythonModule.\n*func* is expected to be a {class}`cgen.FunctionBody`.\nAdditionally, *func* must be a host callable function,\nnot a CUDA \\_\\_global\\_\\_ entrypoint.\n"]}, {"name": "codepy.cuda.CudaModule.generate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Generate (i.e. yield) the source code of the\nmodule line-by-line."]}, {"name": "codepy.cuda.CudaModule.compile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "host_toolchain", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "nvcc_toolchain", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "host_kwargs", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "nvcc_kwargs", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the extension module generated from the code described\nby *self*. If necessary, build the code using *toolchain* with\n{func}`codepy.jit.extension_from_string`. Any keyword arguments\naccept by that latter function may be passed in *kwargs*.\n"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit", "documentation": ["Just-in-time Python extension compilation."], "functions": [{"name": "codepy.jit._erase_dir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dir", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.extension_file_from_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "toolchain", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ext_file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_name", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "debug", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Using *toolchain*, build the extension file named *ext_file*\nfrom the source code in *source_string*, which is saved to a\ntemporary file named *source_name*. Raise {exc}`CompileError` in\ncase of error.\n\nIf *debug* is True, show commands involved in the build.\n"]}, {"name": "codepy.jit.extension_from_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "toolchain", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_name", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "cache_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "debug", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "wait_on_error", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "debug_recompile", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sleep_delay", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a reference to the extension module *name*, which can be built\nfrom the source code in *source_string* if necessary. Raise\n{exc}`CompileError` in case of error.\n\nCompiled code is cached in *cache_dir* and available immediately if it has\nbeen compiled at some point in the past. Compiler and Python API versions\nas well as versions of include files are taken into account when examining\nthe cache. If *cache_dir* is `None`, a default location is assumed. If\nit is `False`, no caching is performed. Proper locking is performed on\nthe cache directory. Simultaneous use of the cache by multiple processes\nworks as expected, but may lead to delays because of locking. By default,\na process waits for 1 second before reattempting to acquire the *cache_dir*\nlock. A different waiting time can be specified through *sleep_delay*.\n\nThe code in *source_string* will be saved to a temporary file named\n*source_name* if it needs to be compiled.\n\nIf *debug* is `True`, commands involved in the build are printed.\n\nIf *wait_on_error* is `True`, the full path name of the temporary in\nwhich a {exc}`CompileError` occurred is shown and the user is expected\nto press a key before the temporary file gets deleted. If *wait_on_error*\nis `None`, it is taken to be the same as *debug*.\n\nIf *debug_recompile*, messages are printed indicating whether a\nrecompilation is taking place.\n"]}, {"name": "codepy.jit.compile_from_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "toolchain", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_name", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "cache_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "debug", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "wait_on_error", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "debug_recompile", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "object", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "source_is_binary", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sleep_delay", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a tuple: mod_name, file_name, recompiled.\nmod_name is the name of the module represented by a compiled object,\nfile_name is the name of the compiled object, which can be built from the\nsource code(s) in *source_strings* if necessary,\nrecompiled is True if the object had to be recompiled, False if the cache\nis hit.\nRaise {exc}`CompileError` in case of error. The mod_name and file_name\nare designed to be used with load_dynamic to load a python module from\nthis object, if desired.\n\nCompiled code is cached in *cache_dir* and available immediately if it has\nbeen compiled at some point in the past. Compiler and Python API versions\nas well as versions of include files are taken into account when examining\nthe cache. If *cache_dir* is `None`, a default location is assumed. If it\nis `False`, no caching is performed. Proper locking is performed on the\ncache directory. Simultaneous use of the cache by multiple processes works\nas expected, but may lead to delays because of locking. By default, a\nprocess waits for 1 second before reattempting to acquire the *cache_dir*\nlock. A different waiting time can be specified through *sleep_delay*.\n\nThe code in *source_string* will be saved to a temporary file named\n*source_name* if it needs to be compiled.\n\nIf *debug* is `True`, commands involved in the build are printed.\n\nIf *wait_on_error* is `True`, the full path name of the temporary in\nwhich a {exc}`CompileError` occurred is shown and the user is expected\nto press a key before the temporary file gets deleted. If *wait_on_error*\nis `None`, it is taken to be the same as *debug*.\n\nIf *debug_recompile*, messages are printed indicating whether a\nrecompilation is taking place.\n\nIf *source_is_binary*, the source string is a compile object file and\nshould be treated as binary for read/write purposes\n"]}, {"name": "codepy.jit.link_extension", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "toolchain", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "objects", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mod_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache_dir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "debug", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "wait_on_error", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "codepy.jit.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.guess_toolchain", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "codepy.jit.CleanupBase", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.CleanupManager", "bases": ["CleanupBase"], "methods": [{"name": "codepy.jit.CleanupManager.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.CleanupManager.register", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "c", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.CleanupManager.clean_up", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.CleanupManager.error_clean_up", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "codepy.jit.TempDirManager", "bases": ["CleanupBase"], "methods": [{"name": "codepy.jit.TempDirManager.__init__", "asynchronous": fal